<p>The NFL has a problem, and it’s getting harder to ignore. Every Sunday, fans watch as star players limp off the field, backup quarterbacks take the helm, and fantasy football lineups crumble. Over the past few seasons, it feels like injuries have become more frequent and more devastating.</p>
<p>But is this just recency bias, or are injuries actually trending upward?</p>
<p>Let’s look at the numbers.</p>
<p>Using injury report data from the past seven seasons (2018-2024), we can track exactly how many games players have missed due to injury during the regular season. The results paint a concerning picture for the league and suggest that the problem isn’t going away anytime soon.</p>
